OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to 'loyal and
OL,4,Cfunny' Race Across the World contestant
OL,6,FThe family of a 24-year-old who
OL,7,Fcompeted in the Race Across the World
OL,8,Fhave paid tribute to him after he died
OL,9,Fin a car crash.
OL,11,FSam Gardiner competed in the global
OL,12,Ftravel competition's second series
OL,13,Fwith his mother, who said she was
OL,14,Fdevastated by his death.
OL,16,FHe had been driving on the A34, in
OL,17,FGatley, Stockport, when his car left
OL,18,Fthe road and rolled before landing on
OL,19,Fits side, leaving him with serious
OL,20,Fhead injuries.
